$Id: PORTING,v 1.3 2002/11/26 06:25:10 deven Exp $

Gangplank has been known to build and run on the following platforms:

 * Linux (i386) - Red Hat 6.x, 7.x; Debian 2.2
 * FreeBSD 4.x, 5.x (i386)
 * NetBSD 1.6 (i386)
 * Macintosh OS X (Darwin)
 * Solaris 8 (SPARC)
 * SunOS 4.1.4
 * IRIX 6.5.6
 * AIX 4.3.2

Gangplank is known to compile with GCC versions from 2.95 through 3.1, using
the "gcc" driver.  (Although Gangplank is written in C++, it does not use the
standard C++ library.)  Gangplank has also been tested with the Sun compiler
under Solaris.
